\rho(X,Y)
E X = 2p^2+2p(1-p)=2p
E X^2 = 4p^2+2p(1-p)=2p(p+1)
E Y=2p^2-2(1-p)^2=2(2p-1)
E Y^2=4p^2+4(1-p)^2=8p^2-8p+4
EXY=4p^2
X
Y
 \operatorname{Var} X = E X^2 - (E X)^2 = 2p(1-p). 
 \operatorname{Var} Y = E Y^2 - (E Y)^2 = -8p^2+8p=8p(1-p). 
 \operatorname{Cov}(X,Y) =E XY-E X EY = 4p^2 - 16p^2(1-p)^2. 
X
Y
 \rho(X,Y)=\frac{\operatorname{Cov}(X,Y)}{\sqrt{\operatorname{Var} X \operatorname{Var} Y}} = \frac{p \left(4p(2-p)-3\right)}{1-p}. 
